-- Malaysia's 1MDB, Australia's Land Lease to jointly develop $2.5 bln property project
-- By Yantoultra Ngui
-- Wed Jun 25, 2014 03:50AM EDT
-- None



KUALA LUMPUR, June 25 (Reuters) - State investment fund 1Malaysia Development Bhd (1MDB) said it will jointly develop 17 acres of land in Kuala Lumpur with Australian property firm Land Lease, and turn it into a retail development worth 8 billion ringgit ($2.49 billion).

The development, dubbed the TRX Lifestyle Quarter, is expected to attract $1 billion of foreign investments, 1MDB said in a statement on Wednesday. It will comprise a hotel, three residential towers and a retail mall.